<p>p>Brilliant post. You must have heard the old saw, there are only two industries that call their customers &#8220;users&#8221; &#8212; software, and illegal drugs.&lt;/p.</p>

<p><p>That used to just be a weak joke, but not any more. When web folk talk shop, the highest praise is to say that that someone&#8217;s site is habit-forming. Highly trained people spend their every waking moment trying to make a media product hit someone&#8217;s pleasure center in just the right way. Is there a real difference between that job, and say, genetically engineering tobacco for a higher nicotine level?</p></p>

